						<summary>

						<p>This is also probably a record of Uttama-Chōḷa. It records a gift of 97 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-Mahādēva by a <hi rend="italic">maṉṟāḍi</hi> (shepherd) of the place named Dēvan Nakkaṉ.</p>						

